name: Legacy-Systems-Modernization
description: Modernized legacy enterprise applications into cloud-native microservices

name: Product-Management-System
description: Product management system using java spring boot and microservice architecture

name: db2-reader
description: Code to support the demonstration of deploying an API microservice and front end on OpenShift to connect to a Db2 database running on AIX on an IBM Power Systems server.

name: FlightsAndSearchService
description: This is FlightsAndSearch microservice for Airline Management System

name: go-async-order-system
description: Async Order System is a microservice-based application developed in Go for asynchronous order management using RabbitMQ

name: recommendation-system
description: Developed a robust product recommendation system through three evolving approaches, enhancing product retrieval with advanced NLP techniques and Qdrant's vector search database, significantly improving performance and scalability.

name: Stock-Control-System
description: Efficiently control inventory with Java/Spring Boot/JSP/Spring Data JPA. Optimize database operations for improved performance. Two Microservices ensure seamless management. Rigorous testing with JUnit and Mockito guarantees reliability.

name: Automated-Deployment-and-Networking-of-Microservices-using-Docker-and-Kubernetes
description: Developed a real-time system to automate the deployment and networking of Dockerized microservices using Kubernetes. The project features a Node.js web service, containerized with Docker, and orchestrated with Kubernetes for automatic scaling and load balancing. Jenkins CI/CD pipelines were configured for seamless deployment automation.

name: alertify
description: A microservices-based notification system built in Golang that delivers notifications via SMS, email, and Slack. Includes an API interface, "at least once" message delivery, and a message broker for reliable message publishing. Open-source license under Apache License 2.0.

name: Task-management-app
description: A real-time task management system featuring a Kanban-style dashboard. Built with Next.js for the frontend. The backend, using NestJS in a microservice architecture, integrates Redis for caching, RabbitMQ for messaging, and MongoDB. Developed with Node.js, TypeScript, Socket.io and JWT Passport for Authn.
